\textbf{Solution:} Let the $x$-coordinate of point $D$ be $x$. Then we have:
\[80(x-1.5)+100(x-1.5)=144\]
Solving this gives $x=2.3$. Hence, the coordinates of point D are $(2.3, 144)$. Let the function of line segment $CD$ be $y=kx+b (k\ne 0)$. Then:
\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
1.5k+b=0\\
2.3k+b=144
\end{array}
\right.
\]
Solving these equations gives:
\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
k=180\\
b=-270
\end{array}
\right.
\]
Therefore, $y=180x-270$. When $180x-270=20$, solving for $x$ gives $x=\frac{29}{18}$. Let the equation for $AB$ be $y=mx+n (m\ne 0)$. Then:
\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
n=180\\
m+n=0
\end{array}
\right.
\]
